pull_request.title: Filters, transparency, hyperparams
pull_request.body:
Made a couple functions if we want to do quick last minute testing.

Transparency now works, but with a hyperparam so you have to choose appropriately when calling `preprocess()`.  Maybe this can be a slider if we need?

New hyperparam list:
- transparent_thresh in `preprocess()`
- `epsilon` in `preprocess()`
- changed `scale_factor` in `detectMultiScale()` -- this affects how well it detects faces at different zooms

Note: the cascading head detector kind of fails when I tilt my head at an angle left/right.
